        "description": "In this comprehensive course, you will embark on a journey to master Microsoft 365 Copilot, an innovative AI-driven assistant designed to streamline your workflow across various Office applications. The course begins with an introduction to Copilot, explaining its different versions and providing an overview of what you can expect to learn. The course delves into the fundamentals of Microsoft Copilot, offering detailed insights into its features and capabilities. You will explore how Copilot works and discover practical applications for this powerful tool. Additionally, an optional primer on Generative AI provides a deeper understanding of the technology behind Copilot, including its benefits, drawbacks, and ethical implications. By the end of this section, you will have a solid foundation to harness Copilot's full potential. Hands-on tutorials cover the integration of Microsoft Copilot with Word, Excel, PowerPoint, Outlook, and Teams. You will learn to draft and edit documents, create complex spreadsheets, design impactful presentations, and manage emails and meetings efficiently. Each section offers practical examples and step-by-step instructions to ensure you gain real-world skills. Whether you're enhancing your Word documents or analyzing data in Excel, this course provides the tools you need to succeed. To access the supplementary materials, scroll down to the 'Resources' section above the 'Course Outline' and click 'Supplemental Content.' This will either initiate a download or redirect you to GitHub. What you will learn Utilize Microsoft 365 Copilot to streamline document creation and editing in Word Analyze data and create complex spreadsheets in Excel with Copilot Design impactful presentations in PowerPoint using Copilot Manage emails and meetings efficiently with Outlook and Teams integrations Enhance collaboration and productivity with Microsoft 365 Chat features Understand the principles and applications of Generative AI Audience This course is for working professionals and office workers who want to get things done faster with Generative AI. This is also for individuals passionate about technology, including and especially those with non-technical backgrounds, seeking to explore Generative AI. This is especially useful for those who use Microsoft Office (Word, Excel, PowerPoint, Outlook, Teams) as part of their job. About the Author HHN Automate Book Inc.: Henry Habib, a top instructor with 200K students, is a manager at a leading management consulting firm, advising Fortune 500 companies on growth strategy, operations, and analytics. With extensive experience in data-driven solutions for both large and small organizations, Henry is a champion of Generative AI and No-Code application development. He integrates these technologies to deliver efficient, comprehensible business applications. As a professor, Henry is dedicated to student success, creating engaging courses and offering continuous support on topics like case interviews, no-code development, and automation.",
        "html": "<span><p>In this comprehensive course, you will embark on a journey to master Microsoft 365 Copilot, an innovative AI-driven assistant designed to streamline your workflow across various Office applications. The course begins with an introduction to Copilot, explaining its different versions and providing an overview of what you can expect to learn.</p><p>The course delves into the fundamentals of Microsoft Copilot, offering detailed insights into its features and capabilities. You will explore how Copilot works and discover practical applications for this powerful tool. Additionally, an optional primer on Generative AI provides a deeper understanding of the technology behind Copilot, including its benefits, drawbacks, and ethical implications. By the end of this section, you will have a solid foundation to harness Copilot's full potential.</p><p>Hands-on tutorials cover the integration of Microsoft Copilot with Word, Excel, PowerPoint, Outlook, and Teams. You will learn to draft and edit documents, create complex spreadsheets, design impactful presentations, and manage emails and meetings efficiently. Each section offers practical examples and step-by-step instructions to ensure you gain real-world skills. Whether you're enhancing your Word documents or analyzing data in Excel, this course provides the tools you need to succeed.</p><p>To access the supplementary materials, scroll down to the 'Resources' section above the 'Course Outline' and click 'Supplemental Content.' This will either initiate a download or redirect you to GitHub.</p><h4>What you will learn</h4><ul><li>Utilize Microsoft 365 Copilot to streamline document creation and editing in Word</li><li>Analyze data and create complex spreadsheets in Excel with Copilot</li><li>Design impactful presentations in PowerPoint using Copilot</li><li>Manage emails and meetings efficiently with Outlook and Teams integrations</li><li>Enhance collaboration and productivity with Microsoft 365 Chat features</li><li>Understand the principles and applications of Generative AI</li></ul><h4>Audience</h4><p>This course is for working professionals and office workers who want to get things done faster with Generative AI. This is also for individuals passionate about technology, including and especially those with non-technical backgrounds, seeking to explore Generative AI. This is especially useful for those who use Microsoft Office (Word, Excel, PowerPoint, Outlook, Teams) as part of their job.</p><h4>About the Author</h4><p><b>HHN Automate Book Inc.: </b>Henry Habib, a top instructor with 200K students, is a manager at a leading management consulting firm, advising Fortune 500 companies on growth strategy, operations, and analytics. With extensive experience in data-driven solutions for both large and small organizations, Henry is a champion of Generative AI and No-Code application development. He integrates these technologies to deliver efficient, comprehensible business applications. As a professor, Henry is dedicated to student success, creating engaging courses and offering continuous support on topics like case interviews, no-code development, and automation.</p></span>",
