        "description": "This course offers an in-depth exploration of GitHub Copilot and ChatGPT, two cutting-edge tools revolutionizing the coding landscape. Starting with a comprehensive introduction, you'll set up your development environment, including GitHub and OpenAI accounts and VSCode installation. From there, you'll delve into ChatGPT, understanding its learning process, crafting ideal prompts, and exploring various use cases such as research, code generation, and explanation. A dedicated section compares free alternatives like Google Gemini, providing a well-rounded perspective on AI assistants. As the course progresses, you'll be introduced to GitHub Copilot, its setup, and functionality. Detailed sections cover prompting techniques, both by writing and using comments, enhancing your ability to communicate with these tools effectively. Practical exercises, like generating a Tic-Tac-Toe game, solidify your understanding and application of the concepts. The course culminates with advanced topics, agents, tips, and a premium ChatGPT workshop, ensuring you are well-equipped to integrate these AI tools into your development practice seamlessly. To access the supplementary materials, scroll down to the 'Resources' section above the 'Course Outline' and click 'Supplemental Content.' This will either initiate a download or redirect you to GitHub. What you will learn Set up and configure GitHub Copilot and ChatGPT Create effective prompts for various coding tasks Utilize AI tools for research, code generation, and explanation Compare and evaluate free AI alternatives Apply learned concepts through hands-on projects Enhance coding efficiency with advanced tips and tricks Audience This course is tailored for developers with at least junior-level proficiency who have basic coding knowledge and are eager to integrate AI tools into their workflow. Familiarity with at least one programming language and a basic understanding of using the terminal are required. All the tools needed for the course are free or have free trial periods, and detailed installation guides are included. About the Author Yaroslav Dobroskok: Yaroslav is an expert software engineer with over 10 years of experience, where he has mentored more than 10 novices who have since become professional software developers. As a leader, he has managed several engineering teams, one of which comprised up to 25 engineers. A passionate advocate of AI, Yaroslav is dedicated to integrating cutting-edge technology into everyday coding practices. Outside of work, he enjoys wakeboarding, scuba diving, and piloting drones, combining his love for adventure with his technical expertise.",
        "html": "<span><p>This course offers an in-depth exploration of GitHub Copilot and ChatGPT, two cutting-edge tools revolutionizing the coding landscape. Starting with a comprehensive introduction, you'll set up your development environment, including GitHub and OpenAI accounts and VSCode installation.</p><p>From there, you'll delve into ChatGPT, understanding its learning process, crafting ideal prompts, and exploring various use cases such as research, code generation, and explanation. A dedicated section compares free alternatives like Google Gemini, providing a well-rounded perspective on AI assistants. As the course progresses, you'll be introduced to GitHub Copilot, its setup, and functionality. Detailed sections cover prompting techniques, both by writing and using comments, enhancing your ability to communicate with these tools effectively.</p><p>Practical exercises, like generating a Tic-Tac-Toe game, solidify your understanding and application of the concepts. The course culminates with advanced topics, agents, tips, and a premium ChatGPT workshop, ensuring you are well-equipped to integrate these AI tools into your development practice seamlessly.</p><p>To access the supplementary materials, scroll down to the 'Resources' section above the 'Course Outline' and click 'Supplemental Content.' This will either initiate a download or redirect you to GitHub.</p><h4>What you will learn</h4><ul><li>Set up and configure GitHub Copilot and ChatGPT</li><li>Create effective prompts for various coding tasks</li><li>Utilize AI tools for research, code generation, and explanation</li><li>Compare and evaluate free AI alternatives</li><li>Apply learned concepts through hands-on projects</li><li>Enhance coding efficiency with advanced tips and tricks</li></ul><h4>Audience</h4><p>This course is tailored for developers with at least junior-level proficiency who have basic coding knowledge and are eager to integrate AI tools into their workflow. Familiarity with at least one programming language and a basic understanding of using the terminal are required. All the tools needed for the course are free or have free trial periods, and detailed installation guides are included.</p><h4>About the Author</h4><p><b>Yaroslav Dobroskok: </b>Yaroslav is an expert software engineer with over 10 years of experience, where he has mentored more than 10 novices who have since become professional software developers. As a leader, he has managed several engineering teams, one of which comprised up to 25 engineers. A passionate advocate of AI, Yaroslav is dedicated to integrating cutting-edge technology into everyday coding practices. Outside of work, he enjoys wakeboarding, scuba diving, and piloting drones, combining his love for adventure with his technical expertise.</p></span>",
