        "description": "Learn the inner workings of Generative AI, from the Transformer and the Attention Mechanism to how LLMs are trained \n Understand differences between popular LLMs and how to implement open-source models using Hugging Face, as well as how RAG works, and some popular methods of fine-tuning \n Learn key tips for Prompt Engineering and the secrets to getting Gen AI to do what you want \n Start developing your own LLM applications with tools like LangChain and LlamaIndex \n \n Most Generative AI courses are either too high-level or too detailed. This course aims to take a balanced approach, walking you through the foundations and giving you an intuitive feel for how the algorithms work before showing you how to build your own LLM applications using open-source models. The course will explore how the foundations of Neural Networks led to the Transformer revolution. The course will delve into the mechanics of key building blocks, such as Word Embedding, the Self-Attention Mechanism, and Retrieval Augmented Generation (RAG). \n Each segment will dive into the concepts before using hands-on examples to show you in real time how to accomplish the tasks you need to learn.",
        "html": "<span><ul>\n<li>Learn the inner workings of Generative AI, from the Transformer and the Attention Mechanism to how LLMs are trained</li>\n<li>Understand differences between popular LLMs and how to implement open-source models using Hugging Face, as well as how RAG works, and some popular methods of fine-tuning</li>\n<li>Learn key tips for Prompt Engineering and the secrets to getting Gen AI to do what you want</li>\n<li>Start developing your own LLM applications with tools like LangChain and LlamaIndex</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Most Generative AI courses are either too high-level or too detailed. This course aims to take a balanced approach, walking you through the foundations and giving you an intuitive feel for how the algorithms work before showing you how to build your own LLM applications using open-source models. The course will explore how the foundations of Neural Networks led to the Transformer revolution. The course will delve into the mechanics of key building blocks, such as Word Embedding, the Self-Attention Mechanism, and Retrieval Augmented Generation (RAG).</p>\n<p>Each segment will dive into the concepts before using hands-on examples to show you in real time how to accomplish the tasks you need to learn.</p>\n</span>",
