        "description": "This course begins with an introduction to the core concepts of Large Language Models and the LangChain framework. You'll start with the basics of forming prompts and setting up your environment, followed by a code demonstration to solidify your understanding. The first section wraps up with a quiz to test your newfound knowledge. Moving forward, we delve into the fundamental concepts of LangChain. You'll learn about prompt templates, chat prompt templates, and the intricacies of working with agents and tools. As you progress, the course covers advanced topics such as document loaders, output parsers, language embeddings, and vector databases. Practical applications, like creating your first RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation) application, are integrated to enhance your learning experience. The final section focuses on real-world RAG applications and projects. You'll work on diverse projects, including SQL data integration, conversational memory, CV search applications, and website query chatbots. By the end of the course, you'll be proficient in analyzing structured data using natural language and creating sophisticated AI-driven applications, ready to apply these skills in real-world scenarios. To access the supplementary materials, scroll down to the 'Resources' section above the 'Course Outline' and click 'Supplemental Content.' This will either initiate a download or redirect you to GitHub. What you will learn Formulate and implement prompts for language models Develop and utilize agents and tools within the LangChain framework Integrate and manage document loaders and output parsers Create and utilize language embeddings and vector databases Build and deploy Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) applications Analyze structured data using natural language processing techniques Audience This course is designed for technical professionals and developers with a basic understanding of Python and AI concepts. Familiarity with natural language processing is a plus but not required. It's perfect for those looking to deepen their knowledge of Large Language Models and the LangChain framework. About the Author Manas Dasgupta: Manas Dasgupta, from Bangalore, the Silicon Valley of India, holds an MSc in AI from Liverpool John Moores University (LJMU), UK. His expertise lies in Generative AI, Machine Learning, and Data Science, focusing on RAG Application Development with LangChain and LlamaIndex, and various supervised and unsupervised techniques. His research includes NLP using Deep Learning, Siamese Networks, and BERT. With over 20 years of IT experience, mainly in Financial Services, he founded Teksands, where his team develops Gen AI applications in the talent space.",
        "html": "<span><p>This course begins with an introduction to the core concepts of Large Language Models and the LangChain framework. You'll start with the basics of forming prompts and setting up your environment, followed by a code demonstration to solidify your understanding. The first section wraps up with a quiz to test your newfound knowledge.</p><p>Moving forward, we delve into the fundamental concepts of LangChain. You'll learn about prompt templates, chat prompt templates, and the intricacies of working with agents and tools. As you progress, the course covers advanced topics such as document loaders, output parsers, language embeddings, and vector databases. Practical applications, like creating your first RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation) application, are integrated to enhance your learning experience.</p><p>The final section focuses on real-world RAG applications and projects. You'll work on diverse projects, including SQL data integration, conversational memory, CV search applications, and website query chatbots. By the end of the course, you'll be proficient in analyzing structured data using natural language and creating sophisticated AI-driven applications, ready to apply these skills in real-world scenarios.</p><p>To access the supplementary materials, scroll down to the 'Resources' section above the 'Course Outline' and click 'Supplemental Content.' This will either initiate a download or redirect you to GitHub.</p><h4>What you will learn</h4><ul><li>Formulate and implement prompts for language models</li><li>Develop and utilize agents and tools within the LangChain framework</li><li>Integrate and manage document loaders and output parsers</li><li>Create and utilize language embeddings and vector databases</li><li>Build and deploy Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) applications</li><li>Analyze structured data using natural language processing techniques</li></ul><h4>Audience</h4><p>This course is designed for technical professionals and developers with a basic understanding of Python and AI concepts. Familiarity with natural language processing is a plus but not required. It's perfect for those looking to deepen their knowledge of Large Language Models and the LangChain framework.</p><h4>About the Author</h4><p><b>Manas Dasgupta: </b>Manas Dasgupta, from Bangalore, the Silicon Valley of India, holds an MSc in AI from Liverpool John Moores University (LJMU), UK. His expertise lies in Generative AI, Machine Learning, and Data Science, focusing on RAG Application Development with LangChain and LlamaIndex, and various supervised and unsupervised techniques. His research includes NLP using Deep Learning, Siamese Networks, and BERT. With over 20 years of IT experience, mainly in Financial Services, he founded Teksands, where his team develops Gen AI applications in the talent space.</p></span>",
