        "description": "Explore the world of Java web services as you learn to build, deploy, and secure APIs using Spring Boot. Starting with core concepts and the differences between SOAP and REST, you'll move through hands-on tutorials covering Spring Framework and Spring Boot, gradually building your skills with real coding exercises and scalable apps. Advance by mastering SOAP services with a contract-first approach, working with WSDL, JAXB, and endpoint setup. Simultaneously, develop REST APIs for a social media-style app, adding features like CRUD, validation, error handling, content negotiation, and versioning. You'll also work with HATEOAS, Swagger, Spring Security, and Actuator for real-world readiness. Finally, integrate databases with JPA, mapping entities and relationships, and exploring Spring Data JPA and Hibernate. You'll also gain experience with Maven, Gradle, REST best practices, and functional programming in Java. Every step is designed to build practical skills and prepare you for professional backend development. To access the supplementary materials, scroll down to the 'Resources' section above the 'Course Outline' and click 'Supplemental Content.' This will either initiate a download or redirect you to GitHub. What you will learn Build RESTful and SOAP APIs using Spring Boot Integrate Java apps with databases using JPA and Hibernate Configure API security with Spring Security Document APIs using Swagger and OpenAPI Implement API versioning and error handling Automate builds with Maven and Gradle Audience This course is designed for Java developers with a basic understanding of object-oriented programming. No prior knowledge of Spring or web services is required, although familiarity with Java syntax is expected. It is ideal for backend developers, aspiring software engineers, or anyone seeking a solid foundation in building modern web services using Java. About the Author In28Minutes Official: Ranga Rao Karanam is the founder of in28Minutes, a leading training platform that has empowered over 300,000 developers worldwide in cloud computing, microservices, Spring, Spring Boot, and container technologies. With a passion for programming, Ranga specializes in consulting for startups, helping them design and build scalable cloud-native applications while adopting modern development practices such as Behavior-Driven Development (BDD), continuous delivery, and DevOps. Ranga holds multiple industry-recognized certifications, including Google Cloud Certified Professional Cloud Architect, AWS Certified Solutions Architect Associate, Google Cloud Certified Associate Cloud Engineer, AWS Certified Developer Associate, AWS Certified Cloud Practitioner, and Microsoft Azure Fundamentals Certified (AZ-900, DP-900, AI-900). Beyond his professional pursuits, Ranga is an avid hiker, cricket enthusiast, and tennis player. He dreams of dedicating a year to exploring the breathtaking trails of the Himalayas.",
        "html": "<span><p>Explore the world of Java web services as you learn to build, deploy, and secure APIs using Spring Boot. Starting with core concepts and the differences between SOAP and REST, you'll move through hands-on tutorials covering Spring Framework and Spring Boot, gradually building your skills with real coding exercises and scalable apps.</p><p>Advance by mastering SOAP services with a contract-first approach, working with WSDL, JAXB, and endpoint setup. Simultaneously, develop REST APIs for a social media-style app, adding features like CRUD, validation, error handling, content negotiation, and versioning. You'll also work with HATEOAS, Swagger, Spring Security, and Actuator for real-world readiness.</p><p>Finally, integrate databases with JPA, mapping entities and relationships, and exploring Spring Data JPA and Hibernate. You'll also gain experience with Maven, Gradle, REST best practices, and functional programming in Java. Every step is designed to build practical skills and prepare you for professional backend development.</p><p>To access the supplementary materials, scroll down to the 'Resources' section above the 'Course Outline' and click 'Supplemental Content.' This will either initiate a download or redirect you to GitHub.</p><h4>What you will learn</h4><ul><li>Build RESTful and SOAP APIs using Spring Boot</li><li>Integrate Java apps with databases using JPA and Hibernate</li><li>Configure API security with Spring Security</li><li>Document APIs using Swagger and OpenAPI</li><li>Implement API versioning and error handling</li><li>Automate builds with Maven and Gradle</li></ul><h4>Audience</h4><p>This course is designed for Java developers with a basic understanding of object-oriented programming. No prior knowledge of Spring or web services is required, although familiarity with Java syntax is expected. It is ideal for backend developers, aspiring software engineers, or anyone seeking a solid foundation in building modern web services using Java.</p><h4>About the Author</h4><p><b>In28Minutes Official: </b>Ranga Rao Karanam is the founder of in28Minutes, a leading training platform that has empowered over 300,000 developers worldwide in cloud computing, microservices, Spring, Spring Boot, and container technologies. With a passion for programming, Ranga specializes in consulting for startups, helping them design and build scalable cloud-native applications while adopting modern development practices such as Behavior-Driven Development (BDD), continuous delivery, and DevOps.\nRanga holds multiple industry-recognized certifications, including Google Cloud Certified Professional Cloud Architect, AWS Certified Solutions Architect Associate, Google Cloud Certified Associate Cloud Engineer, AWS Certified Developer Associate, AWS Certified Cloud Practitioner, and Microsoft Azure Fundamentals Certified (AZ-900, DP-900, AI-900).\nBeyond his professional pursuits, Ranga is an avid hiker, cricket enthusiast, and tennis player. He dreams of dedicating a year to exploring the breathtaking trails of the Himalayas.</p></span>",
