        "description": "Learn core blue and red team security techniques for cloud-based systems and services \n Understand the key differences between on-prem security and cloud security \n Learn the fundamentals of risk management, compliance, operations, monitoring and vulnerability scanning \n \n In today’s world it’s imperative to maintain defensive security for both cloud and on-prem. Whether you’re a cyber specialist or a cloud or DevOps engineer, security is essential. \n Security Engineers -- from red, blue, and purple teams to penetration testers -- need to fully understand how to defend and mitigate attacks in all environments. The course will explore a wide range of topics, from various methods of running infrastructure in the cloud to services like Serverless and source control and API-based platforms like Kubernetes. \n This training will teach you about the core security topics for this work as well as how to take knowledge from on-prem security, implement that knowledge in the cloud, and learn the new methods of securing cloud-based technologies.",
        "html": "<span><ul>\n<li>Learn core blue and red team security techniques for cloud-based systems and services</li>\n<li>Understand the key differences between on-prem security and cloud security</li>\n<li>Learn the fundamentals of risk management, compliance, operations, monitoring and vulnerability scanning</li>\n</ul>\n<p>In today’s world it’s imperative to maintain defensive security for both cloud and on-prem. Whether you’re a cyber specialist or a cloud or DevOps engineer, security is essential.</p>\n<p>Security Engineers -- from red, blue, and purple teams to penetration testers -- need to fully understand how to defend and mitigate attacks in all environments. The course will explore a wide range of topics, from various methods of running infrastructure in the cloud to services like Serverless and source control and API-based platforms like Kubernetes.</p>\n<p>This training will teach you about the core security topics for this work as well as how to take knowledge from on-prem security, implement that knowledge in the cloud, and learn the new methods of securing cloud-based technologies.</p>\n</span>",
